<!-- Full description -->
<section class="bg-slate-50 py-20 dark:bg-slate-800/40">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="mb-10 text-center">
            <span class="text-sm font-bold tracking-widest text-subblue-600 uppercase dark:text-subblue-400">Overview</span>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">How Subchron helps</h2>
        </div>
        <div data-reveal class="reveal-base space-y-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200/80 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-slate-900/5 dark:border-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-800 dark:ring-slate-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Subchron helps improve accuracy in attendance and overtime recording, reduces manual data entry and human errors, and makes payroll preparation faster and more reliable. It increases transparency and accountability through audit logging and promotes the use of digital and automated workforce management practices within the organization.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Tech stack -->
<section class="bg-slate-50 py-20 dark:bg-slate-800/40">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="mb-10 text-center">
            <span class="text-sm font-bold tracking-widest text-subgreen-600 uppercase dark:text-subgreen-400">Technology</span>
            <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Built with modern tools</h2>
        </div>
        <div data-reveal class="reveal-base space-y-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200/80 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-slate-900/5 dark:border-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-800 dark:ring-slate-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">The backend is developed using C# (.NET 9) with ASP.NET Core MVC and ASP.NET Core Web API, while Microsoft SQL Server is used for secure and reliable data storage. The frontend is created using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for a browser-based interface. QuestPDF is used for generating professional attendance reports in PDF format. Integration with external payroll or ERP systems is handled through RESTful Web APIs and CSV file exports.</p>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">These technologies were chosen because they match the system's needs. ASP.NET Core offers strong performance, scalability, and built-in security for handling sensitive attendance data. SQL Server ensures data consistency and efficient transaction processing. RESTful APIs allow flexible and standardized data exchange with other systems. QuestPDF supports clean and structured reporting, and the use of CSV and JSON formats ensures compatibility with many payroll software solutions.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
